# ReMS Full-Stack: ImmuDB Vault, Route API, Redis Sessions, Handlers & Svelte Frontend

This plan covers migrating hardcoded PII/config to ImmuDB, wiring all backend routes+handlers+middleware, verifying Redis session management, and creating a Svelte frontend. Everything is intentionally over-engineered with layered services and middleware.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Scope is large.** This plan touches ~25+ new files and modifies ~5 existing files across backend and frontend. I recommend we implement it in phases, with a checkpoint after each.

> [!WARNING]
> **ImmuDB gRPC dependency**: The `codenotary/immudb` Go client uses gRPC. The existing [go.mod](file:///c:/projects/ReMS/backend/go.mod) already has it. If ImmuDB isn't running, the app will start with a warning and fall back to env vars.

> [!CAUTION]
> **JWT_SECRET in ImmuDB**: The JWT signing key will be read from ImmuDB at startup. If ImmuDB is unreachable, the fallback insecure default from env will be used. Ensure ImmuDB is running in production.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Phase 1: ImmuDB Config Vault

Migrate all hardcoded PII and config values (TTLs, JWT keys, rate limits, password policies) to ImmuDB as an immutable config vault.

---

#### [NEW] [immudb_vault.go](file:///c:/projects/ReMS/backend/config/immudb_vault.go)

ImmuDB client wrapper with:
- `ImmuVault` struct holding `*immuclient.ImmuClient`
- `NewImmuVault(host, port, user, pass, db string)` — connects & logs in
- `SeedDefaults(ctx)` — idempotent seeder that writes default config keys if they don't exist yet
- `GetString(ctx, key)` / `GetInt(ctx, key)` / `GetDuration(ctx, key)` — typed readers
- `SetConfig(ctx, key, value)` — write a config value (for admin API later)
- `GetAuthConfig(ctx) (*AuthConfig, error)` — reads all auth-related keys into a struct
- `GetTokenTTLConfig(ctx) (*TokenTTLConfig, error)` — reads role/device TTL map
- `Close()` — graceful shutdown

Config keys to seed:
| Key | Default | Category |
|-----|---------|----------|
| `auth.max_sessions` | 5 | auth |
| `auth.max_failed_logins` | 5 | auth |
| `auth.lockout_duration_minutes` | 30 | auth |
| `auth.password_min_length` | 12 | auth |
| `auth.password_history_count` | 5 | auth |
| `auth.rate_limit_count` | 10 | auth |
| `auth.rate_limit_window_seconds` | 60 | auth |
| `jwt.secret` | (generated UUID) | jwt |
| `jwt.issuer` | rms-auth | jwt |
| `jwt.audience` | rms-api | jwt |
| `ttl.access.admin` | 15m | ttl |
| `ttl.refresh.admin` | 2h | ttl |
| `ttl.access.manager` | 20m | ttl |
| `ttl.refresh.manager` | 4h | ttl |
| `ttl.access.default` | 1h | ttl |
| `ttl.refresh.default` | 24h | ttl |
| `redis.session_ttl_seconds` | 3600 | redis |
| `cors.allowed_origins` | * | cors |
| `app.port` | 3000 | app |

---

#### [MODIFY] [auth.go](file:///c:/projects/ReMS/backend/services/core/auth.go)

- Add `AuthServiceConfig` struct that replaces magic numbers
- Modify [NewAuthService](file:///c:/projects/ReMS/backend/services/core/auth.go#866-898) to accept `*AuthServiceConfig` instead of hardcoded values
- Replace [getTokenTTLConfig()](file:///c:/projects/ReMS/backend/services/core/auth.go#161-213) to accept a `*TokenTTLConfig` parameter loaded from ImmuDB
- Remove hardcoded values at lines 163-211 (role/device TTL map), 826 ([NewPasswordService(db, 12, 5)](file:///c:/projects/ReMS/backend/services/core/auth.go#450-457)), 842-846 (auth struct init)

