### Phase 2: Route API, Middleware Chains & Handlers

Create the full route tree with over-engineered middleware stacks per route group.

---

#### [NEW] [routes.go](file:///c:/projects/ReMS/backend/routes/routes.go)

Central route registration function `RegisterRoutes(app *fiber.App, deps *Dependencies)`. The `Dependencies` struct holds all service instances and middleware config.

Route tree:
```
/api/V1/
├── auth/
│   ├── POST   /login
│   ├── POST   /register
│   ├── POST   /logout
│   ├── POST   /refresh
│   ├── POST   /forgot-password
│   ├── POST   /reset-password
│   ├── POST   /change-password      [Auth]
│   ├── GET    /sessions              [Auth]
│   ├── DELETE /sessions/:id          [Auth]
│   └── POST   /verify-2fa
│
├── users/                             [Auth, RBAC, Tenant]
│   ├── GET    /
│   ├── GET    /:id
│   ├── PUT    /:id
│   └── DELETE /:id
│
├── restaurants/                       [Auth, RBAC, Tenant]
│   ├── GET    /
│   ├── POST   /
│   ├── GET    /:id
│   ├── PUT    /:id
│   └── DELETE /:id
│
├── orders/                            [Auth, RBAC, Tenant]
│   ├── GET    /
│   ├── POST   /
│   ├── GET    /:id
│   ├── PUT    /:id/status
│   └── DELETE /:id
│
├── menu/                              [Auth, RBAC, Tenant]
│   ├── GET    /categories
│   ├── POST   /categories
│   ├── GET    /items
│   ├── POST   /items
│   ├── PUT    /items/:id
│   └── DELETE /items/:id
│
├── inventory/                         [Auth, RBAC, Tenant]
│   ├── GET    /
│   ├── POST   /
│   ├── PUT    /:id
│   ├── POST   /:id/adjust
│   └── DELETE /:id
│
├── analytics/                         [Auth, RBAC, Tenant, Cache]
│   ├── GET    /revenue/overview
│   ├── GET    /revenue/trend
│   ├── GET    /orders/volume
│   ├── GET    /orders/status
│   ├── GET    /menu/top-items
│   ├── GET    /inventory/turnover
│   └── GET    /forecast/demand
│
└── health/
    ├── GET    /
    ├── GET    /redis
    └── GET    /immudb
```

Middleware chains per group:
- **Public** (`/auth/login`, `/auth/register`, `/health`): RequestID → Logger → RateLimit → CORS → Recovery → SecurityHeaders
- **Authenticated**: Public + Auth → Tenant → Timeout
- **Admin**: Authenticated + RBAC(admin) → Validator
- **Analytics**: Authenticated + Cache

---

#### [NEW] [auth.go](file:///c:/projects/ReMS/backend/handlers/auth.go)

Handler struct with injected services:
```go
type AuthHandler struct {
    authService     *services.AuthService
    sessionService  *services.SessionService
    tokenService    *services.TokenService
    securityService *services.SecurityService
    deviceService   *services.DeviceService
    vault           *config.ImmuVault
}
```

Methods:
- [Login(c fiber.Ctx)](file:///c:/projects/ReMS/backend/services/core/auth.go#1000-1122) — validate credentials, check lockout, risk score, 2FA, create session in Redis, return tokens
- [Register(c fiber.Ctx)](file:///c:/projects/ReMS/backend/services/core/auth.go#903-995) — validate input, hash password, create user + tenant, log security event
- `Logout(c fiber.Ctx)` — revoke session from Redis, blacklist access token
- [RefreshToken(c fiber.Ctx)](file:///c:/projects/ReMS/backend/models/user.go#133-155) — validate refresh token, rotate, issue new pair
- [ChangePassword(c fiber.Ctx)](file:///c:/projects/ReMS/backend/services/core/auth.go#1127-1211) — validate current, check history, update
- [ForgotPassword(c fiber.Ctx)](file:///c:/projects/ReMS/backend/DTO/auth.go#57-60) — generate reset token, store in DB
- [ResetPassword(c fiber.Ctx)](file:///c:/projects/ReMS/backend/DTO/auth.go#62-67) — validate token, update password
- [ListSessions(c fiber.Ctx)](file:///c:/projects/ReMS/backend/DTO/RedisCache.go#195-201) — list user's active Redis sessions
- [RevokeSession(c fiber.Ctx)](file:///c:/projects/ReMS/backend/services/core/auth.go#425-437) — revoke specific session
- [Verify2FA(c fiber.Ctx)](file:///c:/projects/ReMS/backend/services/core/auth.go#1314-1405) — validate TOTP code

